Notes on a Scandal (What Was She Thinking? Notes on a Scandal in the U.S.) is a 2003 novel by ZoÃ« Heller. It is about a female teacher at a London comprehensive school who begins an affair with an underage pupil. The novel was shortlisted for the 2003 Man Booker Prize.A film version was released in 2006 and stars Judi Dench and Cate Blanchett, both of whom were nominated for Academy Awards for their roles.